==English==
===Etymology===
{{Gr.}} [[κόσμος]] (''[[cosmos]]'') meaning [[world]], and [[πολις]] (''[[polis]]'') meaning [[city]], [[people]], [[citizenry]].

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-cosmopolitan.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adjective===
{{wikipedia}}
'''cosmopolitan'''
# [[all-inclusive]]; affecting the whole [[world]]
#(''of a place, or institution'') composed of [[people]] from all over the world
#(''of a person'') at [[ease]] in any part of the world
#(''of a plant etc.'') [[growing]] in many parts of the world; widely distributed

